          <sv:value>&lt;html&gt;
&lt;body&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Form 16&lt;/strong&gt; represent TDS deducted on Salaries
where &lt;strong&gt;Form 16 A &lt;/strong&gt;represents TDS deducted other than Salaries
like Interest on securities, Insurance commission, winning from lottery.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Form 16&lt;/strong&gt; is a TDS certificate issued by an employer deducting
the TDS while making payments to an employee. As per Income Tax Act, every
employer at a time of payment of Salaries shall deduct at the average rate of
income tax computed on the basis of Income Tax slab rates in the force for that
 financial year in which the payments is made on the estimated income of
the assesses but &lt;strong&gt;Form 16 A &lt;/strong&gt;is a TDS certifying the amount of
TDS deducted, Nature of payments and TDS payments (TDS on Interest, TDS on rent)
deposited to Income Tax Department.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Components of &lt;strong&gt;Form 16&lt;/strong&gt; are as&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.    Name and PAN of employee.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.    Name, PAN and TAN of employer&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.    Acknowledgment number of TDS payment deposited with Indian Government 
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4.    Detailed Salary particulars like House rent allowance, Leave travel
allowance, Leave encashment, Pension, Deductions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;5.    Total income and total tax on Salaries thereon&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;6.    Educational Cess and Surcharge if any&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;7.    Tax deducted under section 192(1A)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;8.    Balance tax payable/tax refundable&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  This TDS Certificate also contains a declaration at the end that the person
deducting the tax has deposited the same with the Central Govt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Benefits of &lt;strong&gt;Form 16&lt;/strong&gt; are as&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.    This TDS Certificate contains all particulars and details of the TDS
deducted and deposited. Although a copy of this TDS Certificate is not required
to be furnished at the time of filing of Income Tax Return, the details
mentioned in Form 16 are required to be furnished in the Income Tax Return.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.    This TDS Certificate is the most powerful proof of the Income of an
Individual and the fact that the tax has been paid thereon. Banks heavily rely
on this TDS Certificate to assess the Income of an Individual at the time of
Home Loan application and require any Home Loan applicant to furnish his Form
16 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Form 16&lt;/strong&gt; in case of Job Change&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In case you have changed your job during the year, you are required to
collect this form from both the previous employer as well as the new employer as
you would be filing your Income Tax Returns on the basis of your Form 16.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Components of &lt;strong&gt;Form 16A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.    Name, PAN No. &amp;amp; TAN No. of the Deductor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.    Name &amp;amp; PAN No. of the Deductee&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.    Nature of Payment, Amount Paid &amp;amp; the date of payment&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4.    Receipt No. of the TDS Payment&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An Assessee can verify the particulars of this Tax Declaration Statement by
furnishing the Quarter and the Financial Year, the TAN No. of the Deductor, PAN
No. of the Deductee, Certificate No. and the Total Amount Deducted &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/body&gt;
