        <sv:property sv:name="hippostd:content" sv:type="String">
          <sv:value>&lt;html&gt;
&lt;body&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent Account Number&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;PAN&lt;/em&gt;) is unique
alphanumeric combination issued to all juristic entities identifiable under the
Indian Income Tax Act 19.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 1.      PAN structure is as follows: AAAAA9999A: First five characters are
letters, next 4 numerals, last character letter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 2.      The first three letters are sequence of alphabets from AAA to ZZZ.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.      The fourth character informs about the type of holder of the
Card.Each assesse is uniquely&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt; — Company&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt; — Person&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;H&lt;/strong&gt; — HUF(Hindu Undivided Family)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;F&lt;/strong&gt; — Firm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt; — Association of Persons (AOP)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt; — AOP (Trust)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt; — Body of Individuals (BOI)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L&lt;/strong&gt; — Local Authority&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;J&lt;/strong&gt; — Artificial Judicial Person&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;G&lt;/strong&gt; — Government&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4.      The fifth character of the PAN is the first character&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a)      of the surname / last name of the person, in the case of a "Personal"
PAN card, where the fourth character is "P" or&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(b) of the name of the Entity/ Trust/ Society/ Organisation in the case of
Company/ HUF/ Firm/ AOP/ BOI/ Local Authority/ Artificial Jurdical Person/ Govt,
where the fourth character is "C","H","F","A","T","B","L","J","G".&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;5.      The last character is a alphabetic check digit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Note - Nowadays, the DOI (Date of Issue) of PAN card is mentioned at the
right (vertical) hand side of the photo on the PAN card&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tax Deduction Account Number &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;(TAN)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt; is an
alphanumeric number issued to individuals who are required to deduct tax on
payments made by them under the Indian Income Tax Act, 1961.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 1.      An Assessee cannot obtain a TAN number without having a PAN.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 2.      TAN structure is as follows: AAAA99999A: First four characters are
letters, next 5 numerals, last character letter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 3.      First three characters represent the city or state where the TAN was
issued and fourth character of the TAN is the initial letter of the tax
deductor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial year &lt;/strong&gt;is a period for which your taxes and income
are computed and for which you have to file your return.It is considered from
1st of April of a year to 31st of march of next year. For example FY 2011-12
means it starts from 1st of April of 2011 to 31st of March of 2012. You have to
file the return afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Assessment year &lt;/strong&gt;is the year in which the income earned is
assessed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Please note that Financial Year 2011-12 means Assessment Year 2012-13.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</sv:value>
